    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-12T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4068: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-12T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1136. Referring to telegram to Department from Legation Copenhagen number
                        3721,<note n="8" xml:id="d767fn8">Mar. 8, 3 p.m., <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_672">p. 672</ref>.</note> following message
                    is being despatched by cable to Legation, <pb facs="0786" n="674"
                        xml:id="pg_674"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Your 241, March 8, 1 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>] p.m.<note n="9"
                                xml:id="d767fn9">The same telegram as no. 3721, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_672">p. 672</ref>.</note> A mission
                            including necessary experts will leave here about week for Copenhagen,
                            Stockholm, Helsingfors, Reval to investigate economic military situation
                            and the question of credits. Please prepare useful data, concise form,
                            to hand them on arrival. Chief of this mission is <persName
                                corresp="#p_GLCW1">Lieutenant Colonel [Warwick] Greene</persName>
                            personally known to you.[”]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
